title: South Korea 3 Year Note Yield
description: South Korea 3 Year Bond Yield was 4.15 percent on Tuesday November 8, according to over-the-counter interbank yield quotes for this government bond maturity. Historically, the South Korea 3 Year Note Yield reached an all time high of 6.17 in July of 2008. This page includes a chart with historical data for South Korea 3Y.
